      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "EQUINOX (1) had a tricky draw and ran well to finish second, beaten a neck, (25.90) at Geelong. Solid formlines coming through his last run. Makes plenty of appeal. ASTON LORENZ (5) shows ability but remains a maiden after six starts. Hit the frame again last start finishing second (29.88) at Sandown. Leading chance. WHY MUMMY (7) did a good job to finish second last time out over 460m at Warragul (26.32) in a Restricted WIN, the second top-three finish on the trot. Well placed here and should do much better. SMART ROSCOE (8) makes debut for the Darren Ryan kennel. Start all important and will need some luck getting across from the wide draw. Respect any moves in the market.",
